text.paragraph:
Indications and Usage (
                              1
                           )	09/2017

Warnings and Precautions (
                              5.10
                           )                                     09/2017

list.item:
Maintenance treatment of asthma as prophylactic therapy in patients 5 years of age and older. (
                                 1
                              )

Not indicated for the relief of acute bronchospasm. (
                                 1
                              )

text.paragraph:
For oral inhalation only. (
                              2.1
                           )

list.item:
Starting dosage is based on prior asthma therapy and disease severity. (
                                 2.2
                              )

Discard QVAR inhaler when the dose counter displays 0 or after the expiration date on the product, whichever comes first. (
                                 2.1
                              )

Inhalation aerosol: 40 or 80 mcg per actuation (
                                 3
                              )

Primary treatment of status asthmaticus or other acute episodes of asthma where intensive measures are required. (
                                 4
                              )

Hypersensitivity to any of the ingredients of QVAR. (
                                 4
                              )

text.paragraph:
Most common adverse reactions (incidence >3% and > placebo) include headache, pharyngitis, oral symptoms (inhalation route), and sinusitis. (
                              6.1
                           )
